                     To  navigate  around  the  data,  use the rr command, then
                     place the mouse pointer in the graphics window  and  drag
                     with  the left mouse to rotate the bounding box.  To zoom
                     in and out, drag right or left  with  the  middle  mouse.
                     When  satisfied with the new viewing position, click with
                     the right mouse.

                     To quickly view a series of isosurfaces, enter  a  series
                     of + or - characters, i.e. ++++++++++++++

                     Scripts  using  above  commands  on separate lines may be
                     directed to r3.showdspf as standard  input.   Use  the  ##
                     sign  as the first character on a line to indicate a com-
                     ment.

